<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                    <head>No. 116.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Hall</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-07-11"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 11,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 596.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to Mr. Hosmer’s
                        dispatch No. 817, of the 5th ultimo, in relation to the Spanish Central
                        American line of steamrers and Costa Rica, I have to request you to furnish
                        to the Department as full information as possible in regard to the contracts
                        of the German and English line of steamers referred to in your
                        correspondence with the Costa Rican minister for foreign affairs.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                            Bayard.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>